One of the prettiest and they have complete facilities, toilets, kids playground, so many green benches to take a break from your long walks or eating your lunch. It‚Äôs just beside the Le Bon Marche and walking distance to so many touristy activities!

Sometimes you find you've been walking and shopping and are more than ready to sit and relax for a few minutes. You aren't looking for sitting on the street, even if you could find a bench. This was a wonderful respite. It's didn't have many people in it at he time we were here, but I can see it is used. They have such a nice little playground with it's own set of benches around it too. Every large city needs a selection of pocket parks like this.

There are nicer parks, but given that we were looking for someplace away from the May Day march and subsequent protest, this place suited us quite nicely. Very little is open on May 1st in Paris, including the original park we planned to spend our time at, so we headed for this one and we were pleasantly rewarded with a nice little place for a picnic. Alcohol is not allowed, but if you are dicreet and pleasant, you shouldn't have an issue. We we're not the only ones enjoying a bottle of wine with our lunch.üçûüßÄüç∑üòÅ
